Contents of this library are:

Library Items - includes harcopy reports which were published by or for SMHEA and equipment manuals, plus books published commercially. There are also audio-visual materials and journals.

Paper Files - the collection of hardcopy documents which provide information about Snowy's business from 1949 until 2004, when they were superseded by TRIM electronic containers. Most of these files are stored in Cooma. Some documents have been scanned & saved with the paper files.

Safe Custody Packets - stored in a locked section of the Cooma Archives, these packets contain original contracts and agreements plus associated documents. Most contracts and agreements which have been signed since 2004 are also available electronically in the subject area libraries.

libraries.name: Water Management
libraries.welcomeText:
Welcome to the Water Management Library.

Document content covers managing the supply and quality of the regions water resources to ensure that the water provides a reliable supply for electricity generation, irrigation, riparian and other uses. Water supplies are defined as areas of land over which water flows, catchment areas including groundwater, surface water and water reserves that are used for a water storage reservoir.

Includes the activities associated with complying with quality standards and legislation, developing policy and procedures and monitoring water flow, usage rates, capacity and potential shortages of water. Also includes the measurement and accounting of water resources, providing technical and operational advice on water-related matters, liaison with professional associations in related fields, government, other organisations and community groups, and implementing water licence requirements.

Use the Asset Management libraries for the design, construction and maintenance of water supply infrastructure such as dams, reservoirs, storage tanks, bores, pumping stations, treatment works reticulation and communication networks.

Use the Environmental Management library for developing environmental plans, policies and strategies to protect the region's natural environment.

libraries.name: Environmental Management
libraries.welcomeText:
Welcome to the Environmental Management Library.

Document content covers the function of managing the organisation's operations to minimise the impact on the region's natural environment.

It includes the activities associated with developing and implementing planning frameworks, systems, policies and programs to ensure regional habitats, threatened species and heritage values are protected to meet sound ecologically sustainable development principles. Also includes evaluating the suitability of potential or existing programs and systems, researching specific areas of interest in order to support the development of organisational environmental projects, programs, standards, and guidelines, and obtaining consent for particular uses of land.

Document content covers the function of establishing the strategic direction for the organisation and overseeing the management of its operations.

Includes the activities involved with developing, monitoring and reviewing business plans, strategic plans, corporate plans and other long-term organisational strategies. Also includes the development of corporate mission, objectives, continuous improvement processes, providing insurance coverage, and establishing and changing the organisation's structure. Includes the development of new business ideas and concepts.

Welcome to the Asset Management Library.

This Library covers the function of managing and operating the capital assets of the organisation. Assets are defined as possessions which provide accumulated wealth for the organisation, depreciate in value, and include plant structures, communication networks, specific production assets, information technology hardware, mobile plant and vehicles.

It includes the activities of inspecting the organisation's assets to ensure compliance with agreed standards and objectives, taking out insurance premiums to cover loss or damage, listing asset items and installing equipment etc in position, connecting and adjusting it for use. Also includes the activities associated with the upkeep, repair and servicing of assets, issuing tenders and managing the services and performance of external consultants and/or contractors. Also includes activities which enable or allow operation of the Scheme's assets, thus entitling Snowy Hydro to operate within the Electricity Market.

Use FINANCIAL MANAGEMENT for financial assets.

Use PROPERTY MANAGEMENT for land and non-production buildings

Use PERSONNEL for people resource assets.

Use STRATEGIC MANAGEMENT- INSURANCE for insurance matters relating to the organisation's liability issues

Use ENVIRONMENTAL MANAGEMENT - COMPLIANCE for matters concerning consent for activities as required under planning legislation.

libraries.name: 3. Asset Mgt Technical (Created from 09/16)
libraries.welcomeText:
Welcome to the 3. Asset Management Technical (Created from 09/16) Library.

This Library covers the function of managing and operating the capital assets of the organisation. Assets are defined as possessions which provide accumulated wealth for the organisation, depreciate in value, and include plant structures, communication networks, specific production assets, information technology hardware, mobile plant and vehicles.

It includes the activities of inspecting the organisation's assets to ensure compliance with agreed standards and objectives, taking out insurance premiums to cover loss or damage, listing asset items and installing equipment etc in position, connecting and adjusting it for use. Also includes the activities associated with the upkeep, repair and servicing of assets, issuing tenders and managing the services and performance of external consultants and/or contractors. Also includes activities which enable or allow operation of the Scheme's assets, thus entitling Snowy Hydro to operate within the Electricity Market.

Use 2. Asset Mgt Other Classes (Created from 09/16) for the document classes of Business Process, Operating Activity, Mobile Plant & Vehicles, Market Regulation & Compliance, Strategic Asset Specification.

Use FINANCIAL MANAGEMENT for financial assets.

Use PROPERTY MANAGEMENT for land and non-production buildings

Use PERSONNEL for people resource assets.

Use STRATEGIC MANAGEMENT- INSURANCE for insurance matters relating to the organisation's liability issues

Use ENVIRONMENTAL MANAGEMENT - COMPLIANCE for matters concerning consent for activities as required under planning legislation.

One document class is available - details are:

Document ClassScopeEmailWho can create and modify?Who can read?*
Technical

Technical records that are not managed by other defined classes in "2. Asset Mgt Other Classes" library.

Includes records about acquisition, claims, construction, design, disposal, implementation, inspections testing & monitoring (e.g., commissioning), insurance, investigations & studies (e.g. forced outage management), liaison, maintenance (e.g., routine maintenance & non-routine refurbishment & modernisation activities), manuals, meetings, project management, review & evaluation, risk management and security of operational assets.

Includes videos, 3D models, timelapse photography & UAV footage.

amnewtechnical@ao-docs.appspotmail.comAO TechnicalEveryone
